<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFFB160E1497F8DAFA93FE92" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="600" pageId="5" pageNumber="597" type="description">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFB16031497F8DAFB9AF803" blockId="5.[151,1437,1797,2040]" box="[199,1148,1905,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFFB16031497F8DAFEBFF804" bold="true" box="[199,345,1905,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFB160315F8F8D9FDE2F803" box="[424,516,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,356,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-112@2.[151,1436,345,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. H. (H.) ferreri sp. nov., female; B. H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., male; C. Same, female; D. H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., male; E. Same, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">Figs 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFB16031641F8D9FDBDF803" box="[529,603,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">4A–H</figureCitation>
): Body long oval, convex, black and dull shinny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFFB16001497F83DFE09FE06" blockId="5.[151,1437,1797,2040]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">
Head (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFFB16031546F83DFE97F83F" box="[278,369,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="597">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) transverse, widest across compound eyes. Vertex finely covered with small punctures and each puncture bearing a short, thin seta. Genae and epistoma covered with denser punctures and setae relative to punctures and setae on vertex. Labrum black, narrower than epistoma, covered with bristles of medium length in its apical portion. Antennal tubercles weakly prominent, antenna (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF8160017D4FF3CFC3AFF3E" box="[900,988,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) shorter than head plus pronotum, club composed of four apical antennomeres. Relative lengths of antennomeres: 0.29: 0.23: 0.47: 0.43: 0.37: 0.39: 0.40: 0.37: 0.26: 0.26: 0.43; relative widths of antennomeres: 0.27: 0.24: 0.23: 0.23: 0.24: 0.24: 0.31: 0.36: 0.33: 0.34: 0.35. Antennomere I slightly expanded; antennomere II shortest, about as long as wide; antennomere III longest, about 2× as long as antennomere II, antennomeres IV–VI similar, shorter than antennomere III, antennomere VII about as long as wide, nearly trapezoidal, antennomeres VIII–X wider than long, IX and X shorter than XIII, antennomere XI with apex rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF816001497FE38FF1DFDB2" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF816001514FE38FE7DFE22" box="[324,411,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) about as long as wide, widest at anterior 1/3; dorsal surface covered with dense small punctures and short setae; mediolongitudinal sulcus thin and shallow but visible, both sides with a shallow depression; pronotal groove thin but obvious basally, absent in anterior part, and wide and shallow at lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF816001166FE70FA69FE7A" box="[1334,1423,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Prosternum distinctly raised before procoxae, surface wrinkled with sparse short setae; apex of prosternal process rounded.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C0ABA8A3FFF8160014C7F827FCA6F862" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="598" startId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" targetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF8160014C7F827FCA6F862" blockId="6.[151,1437,1932,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF8160014C7F827FEF2F82B" bold="true" box="[151,276,1932,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="598">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFF816001655F826FD50F82B" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhou &amp; Liu &amp; Huang &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhou &amp; Liu &amp; Huang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[517,694,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeziyangi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
