<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF6160E1497FF3CFCBFFF76" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">
Female (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF6160E157BFF3CFE62FF3E" box="[299,388,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,356,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-112@2.[151,1436,345,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. H. (H.) ferreri sp. nov., female; B. H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov., male; C. Same, female; D. H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., male; E. Same, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598175/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
): Similar to male. Posterior margin of ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF6160E17B6FF3CFBD3FF3E" box="[998,1077,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
) rounded, weakly impressed at middle and covered with sparse long setae. Spiculum (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF6160E16ADFF10FCACFF5A" box="[765,842,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
) slightly tortuous, apex rounded and slightly dilated. Apex of ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF6160E152AFF74FE2EFF76" box="[378,456,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[185,1423,597,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-196@6.[163,1423,597,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov., A–H, male, I–J, female. A. Head and pronotum; B. Pronotum, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Abdominal ventrite VIII; E. Spiculum gastrale; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Same, dorsal view; H. Same, lateral view; I. Ventrite VIII and spiculum; J. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598182/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Fig. 4J</figureCitation>
) with two long and two short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF6160E1497FEA8FA93FE92" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[199,1397,258,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">
Measurements: BL 15.0 mm, HL 2.0 mm, HW 
