<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFF6160E1497FE8DFB75FE06" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF6160E1497FE8DFB75FE06" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF6160E1497FE8DFE28FECF" bold="true" box="[199,462,294,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is quite different from all other Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFF6160E109CFE8CFA8CFECE" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1891" box="[1228,1386,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF6160E109CFE8CFA8CFECE" box="[1228,1386,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
owing to the rows of elytra formed of regular and distinctly shallower foveolated punctures, while the punctures of the rows of elytra are more unordered or strongly foveolated in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="53D483A8FFF6160E17BEFEC4FB6AFE06" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1891" box="[1006,1164,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF6160E17BEFEC4FB6AFE06" box="[1006,1164,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFF6160E1497FE39FDF4FE22" box="[199,530,402,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" type="distribution">
