</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFF6160E1497FE1DFBDEFE5E" box="[199,1080,438,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF6160E1497FE1DFBDEFE5E" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[199,1080,438,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF6160E1497FE1DFEC1FE5F" bold="true" box="[199,295,438,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Biology.</emphasis>
Adults of this species were collected on tree trunks at night (
<figureCitation id="0CEFE4AEFFF6160E1782FE1CFBCDFE5E" box="[978,1067,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,785,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-228@7.[151,1435,705,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitats of new species of Hexarhopalus. A. General environment of type locality of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov.; B. Live individuals of H. (H.) tianbaoyanensis sp. nov. photographed in nature; C. Live individuals of H. (H.) yeziyangi sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598184/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DCCEABA0FFF6160E1497FE70FB60FE7A" box="[199,1158,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="946BF82BFFF6160E1497FE70FB60FE7A" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[199,1158,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis id="A6A02439FFF6160E1497FE70FEA8FE7A" bold="true" box="[199,334,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="600">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet honors Mr. Zi-Yang Ye, collector of the new species.
</paragraph>
